Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York City:
• In Williamsburg, Brooklyn, a three-bedroom, two-bath condo on the East River and close to the ferry, with north- and south-facing floor-to-ceiling windows, a foyer and a washer/dryer in The Edge, a 360-unit, 2009 building with 24-hour doorman service and staff and an underground parking garage.
• In Midtown East, a two-bedroom, three-bath apartment with two balconies, an oak-lined sauna and a dressing room in a postwar doorman building.
• In Chelsea, a one-bedroom, one-bath apartment with high ceilings and lots of light in a 55-unit, prewar co-op with a shared garden.
